Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present to you 9 & 11-13 Mulwarree Avenue, Randwick. Setback from the main road along a leafy street, 9 & 11-13 Mulwarree Avenue comprises two residential apartment blocks with a total of 24 x 2 bedroom units. With elements of Art Deco style, both unit blocks feature desirable red brick construction on a generous 1,305sqm*combined site area with significant refurbishment and development potential. The property boasts a favourable location just footsteps from the light rail station, Royal Randwick Shopping Centre, UNSW and Centennial Park.

The property benefits from the following key attributes:
- 24 x 2 bedroom units across two apartment blocks
- Significant refurbishment and development opportunity
- Situated at the heart of Randwick: close to parks, beaches, universities, shops and dining options
- Convenient location just moments from the light rail network providing direct services to Sydney CBD 
- Amalgamated development potential
- Highly sought-after suburb with strong scope for growth
- Strata plans approved on two separate titles

CBRE, as the exclusive listing agent is pleased to present 2-10 Belmore Road, Randwick. The property is a fully let, North-East facing mixed use freehold building with significant development upside (STCA) 6.2km* from Sydney CBD. The site consists six boutique retail stores and a dance studio occupying the generous space upstairs, generating approximately $468,740* in gross annual rent. Enjoying 490sqm* total site area with rear pedestrian access, the property is opportunely situated on Randwick’s main commercial thoroughfare, benefiting from high profile foot traffic through surrounding infrastructure and local amenity including hospitals, schools, education, and shopping centres.   

Belmore Road is positioned to capitalise on the dense population immediately generated from two shopping centres, Prince of Wales hospital, Sydney Children's hospital, and University of New South Wales all within 1km*.    

2-10 Belmore Road, Randwick benefits from the following key attributes:

•Fully let to seven established and popular tenants
•North-East facing mixed use freehold building with development upside (STCA) 
•Large site area of 490sqm* with rear street access
•Ideally positioned in the centre of Randwick’s main commercial hub, only 6.2km* from Sydney CBD
•High exposure corner location with dual street frontages to Belmore Road (28m*) and Alison Road (7.5m*)
•Height of building limit of 12 metres.
•Floor space ratio of 2:1
•B2 Local centre zoning

2-10 Belmore Road, Randwick will be sold via an Expressions of interest campaign closing on Wednesday 14th of July 2021 at 4:00pm.  

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approx.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive listing agent is pleased to present 85 Gilderthorpe Avenue, Randwick to the market for the very first time. This recently renovated complex consists 12 apartments across two buildings configured as nine-two bedroom and three-one bedroom + study apartments with 12 lock up garages, double balconies, internal laundries, built in wardrobes, and all bathrooms are equipped with baths. 

Furthermore, additional privacy is presented due to no common walls between apartments, the lush gardens are regularly landscaped, and the building is secured by an intercom system. Commanding an 874sqm* site area, the property is situated on a private and quiet street, bolstered by its proximity to prestigious schools, transport, shops, parks, beaches, and Sydney CBD (5km*). 

85 Gilderthorpe Avenue, Randwick benefits from the following key attributes:

•Total of 12 apartments consisting 9 x 2 bedroom and 1 x 3 bedroom + study units with 12 secure lock up garages
•Full renovation completed as recently as 2010
•Premium investment opportunity in Sydney’s desired Eastern Suburbs and being presented to the market for the first time
•Gross passing income of $401,500* per annum
•Significant residential investment in Sydney’s desired Eastern Suburbs
•Positioned in a quiet, private street moments from transport, shops, prestigious schools, parks, beaches, and Sydney CBD
•Strong rental demand in Randwick as 50% of the suburb’s population are currently renting
•Total Floor Area: 1082sqm* (inclusive of common areas and lock up garages)
•Total Unit Area: 732sqm*
•Strata titled, offering multiple use cases including selling down, occupying, or to hold for secure income stream
•Zoned R3 Medium density Residential 

85 Gilderthorpe Avenue, Randwick will be sold via an online Public Auction on Tuesday 3 August 2021 at 10:30am. (Registration, livestream & online bidding available)
Private inspection appointments will be undertaken

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.
